<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1041" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1041">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-05"><hi rend="italic">August 5,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Manager of the Bermudez Company informed Mr. Bowen to-night his
                            superintendent, American citizen, is held prisoner at the Lake, and
                            closely guarded by Venezuelan soldiers. Mr. Bowen will protest to-morrow
                            morning, and request immediate release, stating he does so while waiting
                            instructions.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>